description.narrative: The Project Development Objective (PDO) is to support sustainable land management practices and increase communities monetary and non-monetary benefits in targeted Project areas which are mainly in erosion prone rural upland areas.This PDO is to be achieved through the support of alternative livelihoods and provision of environmental services and through sustainable utilization of wood andpasture products in the long term. The Project will particularly focus on enhancing the financial, economic, and institutional sustainability of land use and natural resources management, and will help build capacities of Albania farmers, community organizations and government institutions to efficiently use EU funding.

Each audit of the Financial Statements shall coverthe period of on fiscal year of the Borrower. The audited statements shallbe furnished to the Bank not later than six months afterthe end of such a period. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Project Steering Committee | Description :The Borrower shall not later than September 30, 2014 establish andthereafter maintain at all times during the implementation of the Project, a Project Steering Committee with composition, mandate,and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Sep-2014

Finance Agreement :Project Technical Committee | Description :The Borrower shall not later than September 30, 2014 establish andthereafter maintain at all times during the implementation of the Project, a Technical Committee chaired by the Project Directorand comprising a Project Coordinator, component coordinators, technical staff from MOE and other agencies involved in projectimplementation; with functions and responsibilities satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Sep-2014
